Israeli Stocks: Delek Israeli Fuel, Mobile Max and Melisron

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-04-06T10:58:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/israeli-stocks-delek-israeli-fuel-mobile-max-and-melisron.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index advanced to the
highest level since Feb. 21, climbing 0.6 percent to 1,334.3 at
1:27 p.m. in  Tel Aviv .  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Delek The Israeli Fuel Corp. (DLKIS IT) advanced for the
first time in six days, gaining 2 percent to 112.80 shekels. The
owner of gas stations said the Israel Securities Authority
removed its opposition for a sale of securities to the public.  Mobile Max Technologies Ltd. (MBMX)   tumbled to the
lowest since February 2010, sliding 13 percent to 0.76 shekel.
The developer of mobile-phone technologies priced an offering of
8.24 million shares at a minimum of 0.8 shekel each, or 8.5
percent below yesterday’s closing price.  Melisron Ltd. (MLSR)   rose to the highest in almost two
weeks, increasing 1 percent to 84.5 shekels. The investor in
malls controlled by the billionaire Ofer brothers is expected to
complete its acquisition of  British-Israel Investments Ltd. (BRTS) 
 next week after conditions of the purchase were met.
British-Israel declined 0.4 percent to 13.55 shekels.  Netex (Net Express) Ltd. (NTX IT) climbed to the highest
since Jan. 27, advancing 4 percent to 12.09 shekels. The
provider of Internet search sites said it received two patent
approvals in Israel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
